body:
I have managed to use `half_float` from http://half.sourceforge.net/ as a tensor output with the code sample you gave me:
```
namespace Ort {
 template<>
 struct TypeToTensorType<half_float::half> { static constexpr ONNXTensorElementDataType type = ONNX_TENSOR_ELEMENT_DATA_TYPE_FLOAT16; };
}
```
```
std::array<half_float::half, 2> _results{};

_outputTensor = Ort::Value::CreateTensor<half_float::half>(
    memoryInfo, _results.data(), _results.size(), _outputShape.data(), _outputShape.size());

_session.Run(Ort::RunOptions{nullptr}, _inputNames, _inputTensor.data(), _inputTensor.size(), _outputNames,
             &_outputTensor, 1);
return _results[0];
```

The result in my test is 0.0001509.


However I don't manage to use onnx Float16 type.

While using `Ort::Float16` I get a wrong result, in uint16_t I suppose.

```
std::array<Ort::Float16_t, 2> _results{};
_outputTensor = Ort::Value::CreateTensor(
    memoryInfo, _results.data(), _results.size(), _outputShape.data(), _outputShape.size(), ONNX_TENSOR_ELEMENT_DATA_TYPE_FLOAT16);

_session.Run(Ort::RunOptions{nullptr}, _inputNames, _inputTensor.data(), _inputTensor.size(), _outputNames,
             &_outputTensor, 1);
return _results[0];
```

Here the result is 2290.

_________


So I have tested to cast it in `onnxruntime::MLFloat16` in order to use its function `ToFloat()` but it is not exported in the symbols. So `ToFloat()` and the `operator float()` don't work.  
I also tried to use `onnxruntime::BFloat16` that has too a `ToFloat()` function and a `operator float()`. It can be used but the result still remains wrong and is quite the same as the one with `Ort::Float16`.

```
std::array<uint16_t, 2> _results{};
_outputTensor = Ort::Value::CreateTensor(
    memoryInfo, _results.data(), _results.size(), _outputShape.data(), _outputShape.size(), ONNX_TENSOR_ELEMENT_DATA_TYPE_FLOAT16);

_session.Run(Ort::RunOptions{nullptr}, _inputNames, _inputTensor.data(), _inputTensor.size(), _outputNames,
             &_outputTensor, 1);

onnxruntime::MLFloat16 mlres = static_cast<onnxruntime::MLFloat16>(_results[0]);
onnxruntime::BFloat16 bres = static_cast<onnxruntime::BFloat16>(_results[0]);
std::cout << "uint16_t " << _results[0] << std::endl;
// std::cout << "MLFloat16 " << mlres << std::endl;
std::cout << "MLFloat16.val " << mlres.val << std::endl;
// std::cout << "MLFloat16.ToFloat() " << mlres.ToFloat() << std::endl;
std::cout << "BFloat16 " << bres << std::endl;
std::cout << "BFloat16.val " << bres.val << std::endl;
std::cout << "BFloat16.ToFloat() " << bres.ToFloat() << std::endl;
bres.val = _results[0];
std::cout << "BFloat16 " << bres << std::endl;
std::cout << "BFloat16.val " << bres.val << std::endl;
std::cout << "BFloat16.ToFloat() " << bres.ToFloat() << std::endl;

return _results[0];
```

The outputs:

> uint16_t 2290
> MLFloat16.val 2290
> BFloat16 2288
> BFloat16.val 17679
> BFloat16.ToFloat() 2288
> BFloat16 1.45648e-33
> BFloat16.val 2290
> BFloat16.ToFloat() 1.45648e-33

Here is the build error concerning `onnxruntime::MLFloat16::operator float() const`

```
[build] /usr/bin/ld: XXXX.cpp.o: in function `onnxruntime::MLFloat16::operator float() const':
[build] XXXX/include/onnxruntime/core/framework/float16.h:34: undefined reference to `onnxruntime::MLFloat16::ToFloat() const'
```
